cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a supervised hashing method for image data sets based on a deep convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions that the proposed model learns hashing code and compact representations of data simultaneously, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on several image data sets, indicating that it may also belong to the categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
